   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Forty-seven THE CRUCIFIXION AND</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>RESURRECTION OF CHRIST Scripture: Rom 4:25 Crucifixion The crucifixion of Jesus is not a sacrifice or a martyrdom, although it is commonly considered to be so.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The crucifixion of Jesus was to redeem sinners and bear the sins of men.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>In this passage, it says that Jesus was delivered for our offenses and raised for our justification.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>His being delivered refers to His going to the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Resurrection On the negative side, the crucifixion of Jesus took away our sins; on the positive side, the resurrection of Jesus justified us.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Through this resurrection we not only receive a righteous position, but also a righteous life the life of God in Jesus Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>This life enables us to live out a kind of righteous life that exactly matches our righteous position.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>How to partake of the crucifixion and resurrection of Jesus</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Develop this point.</S>
   </TEXT>
